:R-HSA-379716  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0006418 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Cytosolic tRNA synthetases catalyze the reactions of tRNAs encoded in the nuclear genome, their cognate amino acids, and ATP to form aminoacyl-tRNAs, AMP, and pyrophosphate. Eight of the tRNA synthetases, those specific for arginine, aspartate, glutamate and proline, glutamine, isoleucine, leucine, lysine, and methionine, associate to form a complex with three accessory proteins. Each of the component synthetases is active in vitro as a purified protein; complex formation is thought to channel aminoacylated tRNAs more efficiently to the site of protein synthesis in mRNA:ribosome complexes (Quevillon et al. 1999; Wolfe et al. 2003, 2005)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Cytosolic tRNA aminoacylation" ;
        dc:contributor      "Reviewed: Antonellis, A, 2008-12-02 16:58:45" , "Edited: D'Eustachio, P, 2008-11-29 15:41:00" , "Authored: D'Eustachio, P, 2008-11-29 15:41:00" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-379716" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-379724/R-HSA-379724> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

